# Title: New Firewall Rule Added In Windows Firewall Exception List For Potential Suspicious Application
# Author: frack113
# Date: 2023-02-26
# Level: high
# Description: Detects the addition of a new rule to the Windows Firewall exception list for an application located in a potentially suspicious location.
# MITRE Tactic: Uncategorized
# Tags: attack.defense-impairment, attack.t1686.003
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/builtin/firewall_as/win_firewall_as_add_rule_susp_folder.yml

ApplicationPath IN ("*:\\PerfLogs\\*", "*:\\Temp\\*", "*:\\Tmp\\*", "*:\\Users\\Public\\*", "*:\\Windows\\Tasks\\*", "*:\\Windows\\Temp\\*", "*\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\*") EventID IN (2004, 2071, 2097) NOT Action=2